@startuml

title Email Reminder Sequence Diagram with Exceptions

actor User

participant "Frontend (Website)" as FE
participant "Apache\n(HTTP Server)" as Apache

box "Laravel Application" #LightGreen
  participant "Middleware" as MW
  participant "Controller" as C
  participant "Inventory Service" as Service
  participant "Messaging Service" as MessageService
  participant "Eloquent ORM" as ORM
end box

participant "Email Service SMTP" as Email
participant "Gmail" as Gmail
database "MariaDB Database" as DB

note left of DB
It is assumed the User is
authenticated/authorized unless an exception occurs.
end note

== Inventory Request Response ==

User -> FE: Submit inventory request
activate User
activate FE
activate Apache
activate MW
activate C
activate Service
activate MessageService
activate Email
activate ORM
activate Gmail
activate DB

FE -> Apache: POST /borrowRequest


alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward request
   
else Route not found
    Apache --> FE: 404 Not Found

    FE --> User: Display error
    
    
end



alt Valid + Authorized
    MW -> C: Pass validated request
    
else Validation/Auth error
    MW --> FE: 4xx Error
    
    FE --> User: Display error
   
end



C -> Service: createBorrowRequest()


Service -> ORM: Check availability

ORM -> DB: Query item


alt DB success
    DB --> ORM: Result
else DB failure
    DB --> ORM: Error
   
    ORM --> Service: Failure
    Service --> C: 500 Error
    C --> FE: Error response
    FE --> User: Display system error
  
end

ORM --> Service: Available?

alt Item available

    Service -> ORM: Save request
    ORM -> DB: Insert

    alt Save success
        DB --> ORM: OK
        ORM --> Service: Persisted

        Service --> C: Approved

        C -> Email: Send approval email

        alt Email success
            Email -> Gmail: Send
            Gmail --> Email: Delivered
            Email --> C: Confirmed
        else Email failure
            Email --> C: Failed
        end


    else Save failure
        DB --> ORM: Error
        ORM --> Service: Failed
        Service --> C: 500 Error
    end

else Item unavailable

    Service --> C: Rejected

    C -> Email: Send rejection email

    alt Email success
        Email -> Gmail: Send
        Gmail --> Email: Delivered
        Email --> C: Confirmed
    else Email failure
        Email --> C: Failed
    end


end


C --> FE: Response

FE --> User: Display confirmation



== Message Reminder Email ==

User -> FE: Open messages


FE -> Apache: GET /messages


alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward
else Route not found
    Apache --> FE: 404

    FE --> User: Display error
   
end



alt Authorized
    MW -> C: Pass request
else Auth error
    MW --> FE: 401/403
    FE --> User: Display error
  
end


C -> MessageService: check timeout

MessageService -> ORM: Get timestamp
ORM -> DB: Query

alt DB success
    DB --> ORM: Timestamp
else DB failure
    DB --> ORM: Error
    ORM --> MessageService: Failed
    MessageService --> C: 500
    C --> FE: Error
    FE --> User: Display error
  
end

ORM --> MessageService: Result

alt Timeout reached

    MessageService -> Email: Send reminder

    alt Email success
        Email -> Gmail: Send
        Gmail --> Email: Delivered
        Email --> MessageService: OK
    else Email failure
        Email --> MessageService: Failed
    end


else No timeout
    note right of MessageService: No email
end


C --> FE: Response

FE --> User: Display status



== User Ban Notification ==

User -> FE: Attempt login


FE -> Apache: POST /login


alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward
else Route not found
    Apache --> FE: 404

    FE --> User: Error
    
end



alt Valid request
    MW -> C: Pass request
else Validation error
    MW --> FE: 422
    FE --> User: Error

end


C -> ORM: Check user
ORM -> DB: Query user

alt User exists
    DB --> ORM: Banned
    ORM --> C: Status

    C -> Email: Send ban email

    alt Email success
        Email -> Gmail: Send
        Gmail --> Email: Delivered
        Email --> C: OK
    else Email failure
        Email --> C: Failed
    end


    C --> FE: Access denied

else User not found
    DB --> ORM: Not found
    ORM --> C: Error
    C --> FE: 404

else DB failure
    DB --> ORM: Error
    ORM --> C: Failure
    C --> FE: 500
end


FE --> User: Display message
@enduml